<br>
Arriving at their destination, Kaly quickly scanned for guards. Some liked to surprise you once in a while and have a see invisibility potion on them. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>You tend to lose your port clients that way</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, she thought with a sigh.<br>
<br>
Kaly stood still for a moment, dazed. Which way was the tree?! <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I can't remember!</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> &quot;Um...&quot;<br>
Kyusz looked perplexed. &quot;Kaly, what's wrong?&quot;<br>
&quot;I can't remember where they are, Ky. For once, all the trees look the same to me!&quot; Her voice rose in panic.<br>
&quot;Calm down girl. Use your tracking.&quot;<br>
<br>
Kalyndria could have smacked herself good. Tracking. Okay. With a sigh of frustration at herself, she put her abilities to use, and finally reached the tree. She raised her hand to knock when a gasp sounded from inside. Kaly pushed open the door, afraid that she'd come to late. The sight that greeted her was not what she expected. Saphron lay on the floor, apparently out cold, with Stormy leaning over her, a bottle of something in her hand. &quot;What's going on?&quot; Quickly Kaly readied her healing spells and went to the cleric's side, while Stormy gazed at Kyusz. Shock would probably be the best word to describe her features.<br>
<br>
&quot;Kyusz, you know Stormygale, yes? The druid over there is Athene, and this is Saphron, both friends of Stormy. Can you help me please? Saphron is the one who knows what needs to be done, and she's out cold.&quot;<br>
