<br>
&quot;You selfish little vixen!&quot; she heard herself blurt out.<br>
<br>
&quot;Erm, Saphron,&quot; came a voice from beside her.<br>
<br>
&quot;No, I will have my say,&quot; her green eyes flashed with a ferocity a very unfortunate few had ever seen.<br>
<br>
&quot;We have chased you from the Karanas to Luclin and back again. We have pined for your pain. We have prayed to any gods who will listen to deliver you from whatever horrible malady it is that consumes you.&quot;<br>
<br>
Saphron walked slowly to where Stormygale was sitting, their eyes even. Stormy watched the cleric almost dumbfounded at what she was hearing. The room had grown silent save for the crackling of the fires, and the echoes of Saphron's voice on the ancient wooden walls.<br>
<br>
&quot;Wha for yu poony lil' runter? Iss all lost,&quot; Stormy said, a single tear streaming down her cheek.<br>
<br>
Saphron brought her own finger up toward Stormygale's chest, pointing at her heart.<br>
<br>
&quot;Only if you let it go, Girl. Don't you see? Look around you, Stormygale. Others may have left you, but we aren't going anywhere. We're here for you. Here and now. Great Bristlebane, would you just let us help you?!?&quot;<br>
<br>
Saphron turned to the silent group, her eyes flashing once again, yet pleading, &quot;Someone go to Skyshrine. Find anything you can about that rogue. Ask the Claw! Anything! NOW!!!&quot;<br>
<br>
Looking back at Stormygale, Saphron took her head in her hands. <br>
<br>
&quot;We'll find your locket Stormygale. I promise. Just . . . let us.&quot;<br>
<br>
She felt Stormy's hand on her back. A brief squeeze, and the druid was out like a light. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=594544" target="top"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:gold;font-family:Garamond;font-size:medium;">Saphron LaFeete</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:purple;font-family:garamond;font-size:small;">High Priestess of Bristlebane </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212128><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stormygalewindrunner>Stormygale Windrunner</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.cpmission.com/graphics/icons/icon45.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 1026<br> <font color=#7A8798>(8/20/03 1:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=109>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> Stormygale awoke to an almost empty room. Saphron was still there. Who knows where everyone else was. <br>
<br>
&quot;ooooohhh,&quot; Stormygale moaned, and the haggard little halfling was instantly at her side. <br>
<br>
&quot;Is it your back again?&quot; she gently asked, and grimaced at the thought of trying to ease that pain again.<br>
<br>
&quot;No. I got the mother of all hangovers. Look out, I gotta go get sick for a while,&quot; she shoved her friend out of her way, and as quickly as she could made her way to the woodpile out back where she got violently ill for about five minutes.<br>
<br>
Wiping the sweat off her forehand, she returned to the blankets to find Saphron waiting with a cup of tea. <br>
<br>
&quot;You have got to be kidding.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;No. All of it, and quickly.&quot; Saphron shoved the tea at her. Stormygale looked at her with pleading eyes. &quot;All and quickly. The longer you wait, the worse it will be.&quot;  Saphron smiled a beautific grin.  Wanting her to wait so she'd puke her guts up again, no doubt.<br>
<br>
&quot;Cruel heartless runter.&quot; But Stormy took the tea and gulped it down and waited while her stomach decided if it was going to stay there. Things were rumbling and gurgling but it finally decided to stay put.<br>
<br>
She sat back down on her blanket and put her head in her hands. &quot;I have no memory of last night. What did I do this time?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You spent the evening screaming about a locket, and spilling brandy all over the place. So you lost your locket. Its a shame but it really isn't a big deal, you know,&quot; Saphron tried to comfort her. &quot;It's just a piece of jewelry and I know it meant a lot to you but to scream and carry on over it is ridiculous.&quot; <br>
<br>
Stormygale took her head out of her hands and looked her friend in the eye. &quot;You don't understand. How could you possibly understand? Don't you have any idea what that locket is?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, yes,&quot; Saphron waved dismissively with her hand. &quot;Portrait miniatures of you and your mother. I'm sorry you lost it, or had it stolen, but it is only a locket.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;No Saphron. It is not &quot;only&quot; a locket. It is all that stands between me and my Teir'dal blood. It was charmed by one of the strongest enchanters who ever roamed these lands before she left this world for another. So it is NOT just a locket. It is my sanity and I'm losing the battle to keep it.&quot; <br>
<br>
Saphron looked appalled. &quot;Abruzi did this for you, didn't she? Abruzi did it before she died. I remember her commissioning those portraits when you and Krewelle and Chantall were getting into such trouble, so long ago. Is this what she was doing?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes. And that locket hasn't been off my neck ever since. I feel it now Saphron. I feel the fire of my father's blood coursing through my veins. It is taking me over. I can't control it. That is why it must be found. I have to find my locket.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
