*based on text-logged conversation* OCC: in-game and out-of game RP now up to date <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#141419><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kandiya>Kandiya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#7A8798>(9/4/03 11:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=118>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> Kandiya wandered the trader stall of the bazaar chatting with whomever she could.  And always trying to get that perfect deal.  If they were asking one price, it was still to high, she would sit and haggle till she could get a price at least 5k lower than what they were asking.  After buying a few things, she decided a trip home was in order.<br>
<br>
Making her way to Shadow Haven, she watched and listened carefully for anyone that appeared to be following her.  Heart raced as she made her way around.  After reaching Shadow Haven she let out a slight sigh. Saying outloud, &quot;To many people want to hurt my children, to many people want to see me in pain, I'm tired of hiding, I'm tired of hiding my children.&quot;  With that she continued on her way to the small shack she had purchased.<br>
<br>
Opening the door carefully and peaking in, Kandiya tried to sneak in the door to set down her bags.  As the door creaked open, the pitter patter of little feet came thumping at her.  All she could think of was INCOMING.  And with that the two little ones knocked her to the floor.  Kandiya smiled and laughed and held them tight.  The smallest was only a yearling.  Small petite like her mother and had the lightest blue skin for a Dark Elf anyone had ever seen.  The oldest was only in his 5th season and was proud, stalkey and handsome just like his father.  Most would think he was just like the other barbarian children....except he was smaller and not as tall as the rest of the children.  As Kandiya tried to stand a hand reached out to help her.  It was her husband, Doslar.  She couldn't contain her smile.  It felt so good to be home and see all of them together.  Kandiya worked on a feast, while the children played in her bags looking for anything and everything that could be a toy.<br>
<br>
Doslar begins to speak softly, &quot;I'm quite tired of keeping our children hidden.  I'm even more tired of not knowing if they are safe.&quot;  <br>
<br>
Kandiya nodded, &quot;I can't agree more, but Innoruuk will not have tainted blood running around in this realm.  I can't even bring myself to imagine what he could.....should I say would do to them.  He has eyes everywhere and until I feel they are safe and away from any harm, I WILL keep them hidden.  At this point with just the two of us, we can not protect them against him.  One day we will sit in a guild hall amongst friends, one day our children will be allowed to play near the trees....&quot;<br>
<br>
Doslar nods and interrupts Kandiya, &quot;But how long is that one day, and do you really think you can trust the guilds out there.  Look at what they have done to us in the past.  Look at all we sacraficed for them only to be shut out and dissmissed.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You have little patients!&quot;  Boasted Kandiya.  &quot;I have been spending a lot of time with members of The Claw.  Trying to get to know more of them and see what they are about.  Between hunting and trying to provide things for the kids, it's been rough getting to go hunt with them, but everything takes time.  I spoke some with Merci about applying to them.  Who knows maybe we will enjoy their company as much as they would enjoy ours.&quot;  Kandiya sets the plates down on the table and calls the children to eat.  <br>
<br>
Doslar scratches at his face, &quot;Hmmm, I remember Gnomercy saying something a long while back abou them.  He highly recommended talking with them and working on joining.  I just dismissed it at the time, figured a guild like that would have little use for us.  We will see how things go.  It never hurts to make new friends, even if we don't share a guild hall with them.&quot;<br>
<br>
Everyone was done eating and Kandiya was searcing for a bag she had stashed in the wood bin outside of the hut before coming in.  Bringing the large bag inside she set it down on the floor.<br>
<br>
&quot;I figured everyone would enjoy these.&quot;<br>
<br>
And with that she pulls some of the finest pelts around.  Helping the children make beds out of the new pelts she smiles and giggles quietly.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sleep well my children.  Tomorrow I will go looking for a few things in the bazaar, maybe even find a few toys.&quot;<br>
<br>
With that being said the children squeal wildly and lay back down.<br>
<br>
Looking over at Doslar Kandiya smiles softly, &quot;Tomorrow is going to be another long day, we should head to bed as well.&quot;  <br>
<br>
Doslar nods and calls his warder inside, &quot;One day, we will have no fear, one day....&quot;<br>
